<subSubSection id="69AF63ABE647A3DBE2D4A3E871AF7D0D" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A97BE74D8E55C71D1D625D8FFADB4E8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D9CC768E3841E73C6480C3A4ABAA262" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
The authors name the species in recognition of Francis Luma Ewome, locally well known as 
<normalizedToken id="979C35DD69ED518CFCFE00EDAB17BD61" originalValue="‘Escobar’">'Escobar'</normalizedToken>
, a very well trained guide on Mount Cameroon. Over the years, he became instrumental in organising and implementing the field expeditions, and also became a good friend to the last three authors of this paper. It could be stated that the research would have been extremely difficult without the selfless help of Escobar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
